Package org.pircbotx.hooks.events

Class Summary
ActionEvent Called whenever an ACTION is sent from a user.
ChannelInfoEvent After calling the listChannels() method in PircBotX, the server will start to send us information about each channel on the server.
ConnectEvent This method is called once the PircBotX has successfully connected to the IRC server.
DeopEvent Called when a user (possibly us) gets operator status taken away.
DeVoiceEvent Called when a user (possibly us) gets voice status removed.
DisconnectEvent This method carries out the actions to be performed when the PircBotX gets disconnected.
FileTransferFinishedEvent This method gets called when a DccFileTransfer has finished.
FingerEvent This method is called whenever we receive a FINGER request.
IncomingChatRequestEvent This method will be called whenever a DCC Chat request is received.
IncomingFileTransferEvent This method is called whenever a DCC SEND request is sent to the PircBotX.
InviteEvent Called when we are invited to a channel by a user.
JoinEvent This method is called whenever someone (possibly us) joins a channel which we are on.
KickEvent This method is called whenever someone (possibly us) is kicked from any of the channels that we are in.
MessageEvent Used whenever a message is sent to a channel.
ModeEvent Used when the mode of a channel is set.
MotdEvent  
NickChangeEvent This method is called whenever someone (possibly us) changes nick on any of the channels that we are on.
NoticeEvent This method is called whenever we receive a notice.
OpEvent Called when a user (possibly us) gets granted operator status for a channel.
PartEvent This method is called whenever someone (possibly us) parts a channel which we are on.
PingEvent This method is called whenever we receive a PING request from another user.
PrivateMessageEvent This method is called whenever a private message is sent to the PircBotX.
QuitEvent This method is called whenever someone (possibly us) quits from the server.
RemoveChannelBanEvent Called when a hostmask ban is removed from a channel.
RemoveChannelKeyEvent Called when a channel key is removed.
RemoveChannelLimitEvent Called when the user limit is removed for a channel.
RemoveInviteOnlyEvent Called when a channel has 'invite only' removed.
RemoveModeratedEvent Called when a channel has moderated mode removed.
RemoveNoExternalMessagesEvent Called when a channel is set to allow messages from any user, even if they are not actually in the channel.
RemovePrivateEvent Called when a channel is marked as not being in private mode.
RemoveSecretEvent Called when a channel has 'secret' mode removed.
RemoveTopicProtectionEvent Called when topic protection is removed for a channel.
ServerPingEvent The actions to perform when a PING request comes from the server.
ServerResponseEvent This is called when we receive a numeric response from the IRC server.
SetChannelBanEvent Called when a user (possibly us) gets banned from a channel.
SetChannelKeyEvent Called when a channel key is set.
SetChannelLimitEvent Called when a user limit is set for a channel.
SetInviteOnlyEvent Called when a channel is set to 'invite only' mode.
SetModeratedEvent Called when a channel is set to 'moderated' mode.
SetNoExternalMessagesEvent Called when a channel is set to only allow messages from users that are in the channel.
SetPrivateEvent Called when a channel is marked as being in private mode.
SetSecretEvent Called when a channel is set to be in 'secret' mode.
SetTopicProtectionEvent Called when topic protection is enabled for a channel.
TimeEvent This method is called whenever we receive a TIME request.
TopicEvent This method is called whenever a user sets the topic, or when PircBotX joins a new channel and discovers its topic.
UnknownEvent This method is called whenever we receive a line from the server that the PircBotX has not been programmed to recognise.
UserListEvent This method is called when we receive a user list from the server after joining a channel.
UserModeEvent Called when the mode of a user is set.
VersionEvent This method is called whenever we receive a VERSION request.
VoiceEvent Called when a user (possibly us) gets voice status granted in a channel.
